      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index RH, directly used in the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate). Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged scalar stress and exposure time, both mechanistically linked to red blood cell damage."
